<br>
The only need to do so, would come from someone who has become a part of an organization that needs to be defended due to actions of their own.  If you hold yourself and your comrades to a high enough standard, there wouldn't be need to disassociate yourself from your current guild's reputation.<br>
<br>
When the satisfaction of a few begins to outweigh the comfort and enjoyment of the majority in your value system, then you have become a truely selfish individual.<br>
<br>
My comments are directed at no one or guild or player in particualr, just my 2 cents on this post and subject.<br>
<br>
I feel that some of you above are tring to justify to yourselves more than anything, your greed and desire for glory, which is causing you a total lack of concern for your fellow citizens in Norath.  If we aren't as individuals responsible for the organizations that we join, then Who is?<br>
<br>
     Wulfkin<br>
