That is an excellent point, prolly the best on this thread.  But I have to disagree.<br>
<br>
This is a game, not real life.  You cannot compare a guild to an organization.  Like I said, some people play to win.  I may not be one of those people (actually I can tell you in all certainty that I'm not) and you might not be one of those people, but they are out there.  Why should we judge them for wanting to beat the game?  Not everyone can think like ourselves, as much as we'd all wish it. <p><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>
